# Model keys / agent overrides for the LOCAL ephemeral gateway.
# Copy to local.env (gitignored). The gateway boots + the bridge pairs + the
# media share is testable even with this EMPTY — but the agent can only run a
# real model turn (produce files, answer prompts) once a model is configured.
#
# A production agent may use openai-codex via OAuth (those creds live in that
# gateway's .openclaw and are not portable). For a local agent, the simplest is
# an API-key provider:
#
#   OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...      # then point the agent's model at openrouter
#
# (Agent/model wiring for a pristine gateway is configured via openclaw.json /
# `onboard`; see README. Leave empty to validate the media-share plumbing only.)
